<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="33" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,158,652]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,481,374,400]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[489,517,374,400]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="P. G. Ribeiro, Seigler &amp; Ebinger" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Jacquin" baseAuthorityYear="1760" box="[517,714,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Piptadenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="16" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="retusa">
<emphasis box="[517,714,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Piptadenia retusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the Caatinga phytogeographic domain, being found in the states of 
<collectingRegion box="[315,410,410,436]" country="Brazil" name="Alagoas" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Alagoas</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[423,491,410,436]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[505,573,410,436]" country="Brazil" name="Ceara" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Ceará</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[587,674,410,436]" country="Brazil" name="Paraiba" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Paraíba</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[688,831,410,436]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[845,905,410,436]" country="Brazil" name="Piaui" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Piauí</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[919,1163,410,437]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Norte" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Rio Grande do Norte</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1222,1307,410,436]" country="Brazil" name="Sergipe" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Sergipe</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cardoso, D. B. O. S. &amp; Queiroz, L. P." pageId="16" pageNumber="33" pagination="379 - 391" refId="ref15000" refString="Cardoso, D. B. O. S. &amp; Queiroz, L. P. (2007) Diversidade de Leguminosae nas Caatingas de Tucano, Bahia: Implicacoes para a fitogeografia do Semiarido do Nordeste do Brasil. Rodriguesia 58: 379 - 391. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 7860200758212" type="journal article" year="2007">Cardoso &amp; Queiroz 2007</bibRefCitation>
). In the study area, it was collected in the interior of the forest, at 
<specimenCount box="[1030,1108,446,473]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33" type="generic">
<quantity box="[1030,1104,446,473]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="900.0">900 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,158,652]" box="[189,751,482,508]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,351,482,508]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Registered with flower in February.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,158,652]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,486,518,544]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Taxonomic discussion:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="P. G. Ribeiro, Seigler &amp; Ebinger" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Jacquin" baseAuthorityYear="1760" box="[486,684,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Piptadenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="16" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="retusa">
<emphasis box="[486,684,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Piptadenia retusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized, mainly, by the arboreous habit, branches with the presence of aculeous and inflorescences in axillary spike, differentiating itself from the other 
<taxonomicName box="[1199,1379,554,580]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis box="[1199,1289,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">Mimosa</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in the studied area by the presence of extrafloral nectary in the petiole and legume 
<typeStatus box="[1012,1060,591,617]" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">type</typeStatus>
fruit 
<emphasis box="[1125,1155,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="33">vs.</emphasis>
extrafloral nectary absent and craspédio fruit.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
